# Keep build context small — exclude everything not needed by the
# Dockerfile. The Dockerfile itself doesn't COPY anything into the
# image, but Docker still scans the context, so trimming it speeds up
# `docker build`. More importantly, if future versions of the
# Dockerfile add ``COPY . .`` for dev workflows, secret files in the
# context would be embedded into the image — these patterns prevent
# that from happening accidentally.

# === SECRETS — keep these at the top, never weaken ===
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*credentials*
.aws
.ssh
.netrc
hf_token*
infra/*.pem
infra/.terraform
infra/terraform.tfstate*
infra/.terraform.lock.hcl

# === Standard exclusions ===
.git
.github
.venv
.coverage
__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.so
build
dist
*.egg-info

# Heavy submodules / vendored sources that aren't needed for the
# runtime image (the image installs glq from PyPI).
ATLAS
Optimizing-GPU-Kernels
mamba
sglang

# Prototype / scratch files
golay-leech-quant-prototype*.py
modelcard
=0.2.7

# Local model checkpoints + benchmark caches (huge)
*.safetensors
*.pt
hf_cache
benchmarks/results
cache_params,
